    <h3><inlineCode parentName="h3">{`.debounce()`}</inlineCode></h3>
    <p>{`In electrical engineering, when a switch opens and closes, the switch contacts can bounce off each other before the switch completely transitions to an on or off state. The bouncing action can produce transient signals that do not represent a true change in state. When reproducing switch logic, it's important to filter out transient signals by using `}<em parentName="p">{`debounce`}</em>{`, which adds the element of `}<em parentName="p">{`time`}</em>{` to the equation.`}</p>
    <p>{`A time value is emitted if (0) isn't emitted immediately. If (1) is emitted with the time threshold (x `}{`*`}{` 10), the emitted value is now re-calculated and (1) appears shortly later in the downstream publisher.`}</p>
